title: Cyber Security
description: Cyber security isn’t just about protecting credit card numbers. Our undergraduate and postgraduate network security and cyber security courses equip graduates with the skills to protect the ongoing prosperity and health of our society. Everything from business, politics, democracy and the economy, is reliant on safe and secure networks.

title: Computer Science
description: An undergraduate degree must be about more than just knowledge – it’s also job readiness, professional experience and access to further opportunities.

title: Data Management
description: Talented people are needed to learn data management and database administration. Tackling the challenges and identifying opportunities that the massive influx of data presents is a vital skill that is growing in demand. That’s why we offer data management courses

title: Software Design
description: Our artificial intelligence (AI) and software design courses give you the skills to design software for the 21st century. You’ll learn about big data, green computing and cybersecurity, and how they impact on the way we design and consume technology

title: IT Network Design and Technology
description: Our IT networking courses teach you the latest in network technology and design.Understand everything from the basics of computer networks through to the ways local and global digital networks interact — and then learn how to improve them.

title: Data Analytics
description: At Swinburne, our big data course and data analytics degree will give you the frameworks you need to solve big problems with big data. You’ll learn what is needed, what can be ignored, and how to find the data that gives you the answers you’re looking for.

title: Computer Systems Technology
description: Our computer systems courses help you  excel in installing and administering networks, including servers, desktop deployments, robotics-related programming and more.
